cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE. 

The paper proposes a novel deep learning-based approach for salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The approach involves attention mechanisms and loss functions, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents experimental results on six datasets, which suggests the use of multimedia (cs.MM) techniques. Finally, the approach involves the use of a purificatory mechanism and structural similarity loss, which are specific to this paper and may suggest the use of neural networks (cs.NE).
